<div id="review_2317222321" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2317222321" />
    <a title="Emma" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/97039-emma"><img alt="Emma" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1502092437p2/97039.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2317222321?book_show_action=true">Aug 02, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Emma" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Emma" href="/user/show/97039-emma">Emma</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780140039597" href="/book/show/2310554.A_Universal_History_of_Infamy">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/97039-emma?shelf=literature-iberian">literature-iberian</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/97039-emma?shelf=characters-crossover">characters-crossover</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/97039-emma?shelf=short-stories">short-stories</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/97039-emma?shelf=biography">biography</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2317222321" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9584264693944275699">A collection of biographies. Only one of the stories is a Borges original. For rest these are Borges&apos; depictions of a tale someone else has told (my copy had the list of stories this book was derived from). The first three stories, were strong in style and word choices, and interesting in their characterization, although their ending at times simply had the villain dying. Some other stories seemed somewhat lackluster, like the Billy the Kid one, which felt as if much was omitted. <br/>This collection</span>
  <span id="freeText9584264693944275699" style="display:none">A collection of biographies. Only one of the stories is a Borges original. For rest these are Borges' depictions of a tale someone else has told (my copy had the list of stories this book was derived from). The first three stories, were strong in style and word choices, and interesting in their characterization, although their ending at times simply had the villain dying. Some other stories seemed somewhat lackluster, like the Billy the Kid one, which felt as if much was omitted. <br />This collection of stories is an interesting read to get acquainted to the early writings of Borges. Some of his later magic, at times, is foreshadowed here, in the plot more than in the writing style. It is an easier read too than some of his later works, as there's no math, little in the way of philosophy, and it requires little mental processing of the reader. <br />So, not Borges' best work. If you only read one Borges in your life, this is not the one to pick up. His true exhilarating Borges-ness becomes much stronger in his later work.</span>
  <a data-text-id="9584264693944275699" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


