              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4259008176522006580">By his own admission, Borges was an avid reader of encyclopedias and epics of every literate culture, and this passion infuses every page of his writing. Though not as striking as his later work, these early narratives give us the seeds of what would become an intoxicating mind.</span>

