<div id="review_109555232" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/109555232" />
    <a title="Rise" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/2964113-rise"><img alt="Rise" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1624467854p2/2964113.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/109555232?book_show_action=true">Jul 01, 2010</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Rise" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Rise" href="/user/show/2964113-rise">Rise</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780140180336" href="/book/show/2310552.A_Universal_History_of_Infamy">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2964113-rise?shelf=shelfari-favorite">shelfari-favorite</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer109555232" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17517226023475138115">A catalog of bad persons and their wrongdoings. Entertaining and funny, and sometimes scary. There are many novels inside this encyclopedia novel. The tradition of writing down personal histories in compressed form (vignettes), popularized here by Borges, clearly extends to contemporary writers. Cases in point: <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/1178230.Nazi_Literature_in_the_Americas' title='Nazi Literature in the Americas by Roberto Bolaño' rel='nofollow noopener'>Nazi Literature in the Americas</a> and <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/529078.Written_Lives' title='Written Lives by Javier Marías' rel='nofollow noopener'>Written Lives</a>. In these histories are multifaceted representations of multi-faced evil and vanity, potent even in small doses.</span>
  <span id="freeText17517226023475138115" style="display:none">A catalog of bad persons and their wrongdoings. Entertaining and funny, and sometimes scary. There are many novels inside this encyclopedia novel. The tradition of writing down personal histories in compressed form (vignettes), popularized here by Borges, clearly extends to contemporary writers. Cases in point: <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/1178230.Nazi_Literature_in_the_Americas" title="Nazi Literature in the Americas by Roberto Bolaño" rel="nofollow noopener">Nazi Literature in the Americas</a> and <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/529078.Written_Lives" title="Written Lives by Javier Marías" rel="nofollow noopener">Written Lives</a>. In these histories are multifaceted representations of multi-faced evil and vanity, potent even in small doses.</span>
  <a data-text-id="17517226023475138115" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


